ng intergenerational conflicts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aIntergenerational relations. 0aLanguage and culture. 0aLanguage and languagesxAge differences. 0aSociolinguistics. 4aAltern. 4aGenerationsbeziehung. 4aKommunikation. 4aKultur. 4aSoziolinguistik. 4aSprache. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aDiscourse Analysis.  aSociolinguistics.1 aAbdul Hamid, Bahiyah Dato’ Hj., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArdington, Angela M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBakar, Kesumawati Abu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorodo, Michał, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowie, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCortese, Giuseppina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuszak, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuszak, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGiles, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamilton, Heidi E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHelmle, Jill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiełkiewicz-Janowiak, Agnieszka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOkulska, Urszula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOkulska, Urszula, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSeebus, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTieken-Boon van Ostade, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook pac